voice_to_text: Uh, there was a point in my life where I was homeless, and there was a point in my life when I couldn't afford food. Same time, obviously. Uh, and you know who fed me the most? Arabs and Arab men. Specifically. The people that treated me with the most respect, the most consistent respect, and the most kindness were Arabs. Specifically Arab men. I knew that if I begged in the fancier white area that I could get to, in the area near the commuter trains, nobody acknowledged I existed. They walked by me, they didn't see me. And if you can't afford to give someone something and you don't wanna make eye contact, whatever. I'm not here to please. How you interact with people. But these are people I knew could give. These are people I would see go in and pull out a lot of money, and I'll be like, hey, can you buy me something? They be like, I don't have money. And it's like, okay, whatever. Like, you don't have to give me anything. But they never would. Like, they rarely would. But I could walk not too far away and go into an Arab neighborhood with Arab restaurants and Arab shops, and I didn't even have to ask. I could walk through the neighborhoods and people would be like, do you need to eat? They never asked me if I was hungry. They never asked me if I had money. Do you need to Eat. And they would feed me and they wouldn't feed me crap either. It wasn't yesterday's bread or a peanut butter and jelly sandwich. It was a heaping to go container of the best foods that they like. But I remember one time this guy said, let me get you some food, you look hungry. And I was like, I'm so hungry. And he brought me food and he brought me an entire picture of water to sit and drink. Cause it was not the best day and I needed a lot of water.

القيمة السوقية للرجل في المجتمع تحددها ثلاث عوامل و هي: المال، المنصب، الشهرة.  أما القيمة السوقية للأنثى فتأتي من ثلاث خصائص و هي: صغر السن، الجمال، العفة. فالرجل يكون مطلوبا إذا كان لديه مستقبل، بينما الأنثى تكون مرغوبة إذا لم يكن لديها ماض. و الرجل كلما كان محاطا بالنساء أكثر زاد عليه الطلب و تنافست النسوة فيما بينهن للظفر بقلبه لأنه سيد الرجال، أما المرأة فعلى العكس تماما إذ كلما كانت بعيدة عن الرجال كلما كلما كانت مرغوبة لكونها شريفة عفيفة. فالرجل حينما يكون وحيدا تزهد فيه النساء، و ما أن يرتبط حتى تأتيه أفضل العروض من أقوى الأندية. و معظم النساء يفتخرن دوما بالمستوى المادي و المكانة الاجتماعية  لأزواجهن، لكن نادرا ما تجد امرأة تفتخر بأخلاق زوجها و تدينه و علمه. و الرجال الضعفاء يصنعون نسويات مسترجلات، بينما الرجال الأقوياء يخلقون نساءا أنثويات، فالمرأة تخضع للرجل ذي الشخصية الكاريزمية القيادية، و تتمرد على الرجل المنبطح المتساهل المستهتر الذي يعاني من خور في الشخصية و خلل في تقدير الذات و الثقة في النفس. ألم تر أنه حينما يخون الفقير زوجته فإنها تقول لصديقتها: لقد خانني الوغد. أما حينما يخون الثري زوجته فإنها تقول: الحقيرة تريد سرقة زوجي.  فالمرأة تنجذب للرجل المتصف بالثالوث المظلم في علم النفس و هو: الميكيافيلية، النرجسية، السكوباتية، و هذه الصفات لا يستطيع الذكر العادي البسيط التظاهر بها لأن المرأة لديها حاسة سادسة قوية تمكنها من التمييز بسهولة بين الرجل القوي و الرجل الضعيف. و جدير بالذكرأن الأنثى تولد جاهزة في القمة و كلما تقدم بها السن فقدت جمالها و خصوبتها و بالتالي انخفضت قيمتها السوقية في المجتمع، بينما الرجل يولد في القاع و الحضيض و إذا تلقى المعرفة الصحيحة و الارشاد الملائم و التوجيه الفعال فإنه كلما تقدم به السن كلما زاد ماله و جاهه و نفوذه و بالتالي عظمت قيمته السوقية في المجتمع، فالأنثى ينتهي غالبا عصرها الذهبي المزهر في الثلاثين، بينما الرجل لا يبدأ أصلا عصره الذهبي المزدهر إلا بعد الثلاثين و أحيانا بعد الأربعين، ففي الوقت الذي تحصل voice_to_text: Did y'all hear that Jelly Roll is being sued by Jelly No Space Roll? And let me just explain how stunned I am by what Jelly Roll's response was. The man who is sweeping country music awards right now is being taken to court by a wedding band based in Pennsylvania called Jelly Roll. Band member Kurt said the solo singer Jelly Roll is infringing on the group's trademark. He is seeking an injunction and wants Jelly Roll to stop going by Jelly Roll. The band started using the name in the 80s, before Jason Bradley Deford was born. They trademarked the name in 2010 and renewed again in 2019. Jelly Roll, a singer, has talked about how his mom gave him this nickname as a child, but he started using it around 2010 for music distribution purposes. They indicate in the lawsuit, the prior to Jelly Roll Singer success, if you Google them, you could. Now that he has risen to fame, you have to work much harder to find them. So they sent a cease and desist letter to Jelly Roll, whose team was like, let's discuss this. And basically his team said, listen, are you actually competition here? What? The way that that is so ferocious and accurate all at the same time. I cannot. So Jelly No Space Roll is saying that Jelly Space Roll is getting ready to go on a national tour, which just happened to go through Philadelphia. Whoo! A territory war is Even marketing it with the name Jelly Roll. They say that Jelly Rolls unapologetic infringement is causing confusion because we made mistake them. What? His lawsuit is honestly very dramatic, and I love it. In conclusion, the band feels like Jelly Roll is creating unfair competition, and they would like him to find a new name again. I would just argue no one is confused here. Literally no one. But now we wait for a response. Stay tuned.

voice_to_text: Breaking news they have now revealed the cause of death for the boy who has found a sea set trails Carolina Youth Camp. Trails Carolina is a camp for troubled youth. The victim in this case was sent there by his parents. As you may recall, back in February, the boy was found deceased by one of the camp counselors. They said he was located after a round of wellness checks were performed throughout the evening. Now officials say that the boy most likely passed due to suffocation. In the report it asked one of the staff members if they believe the child suffocated and they said quote, yes. The boy was told to sleep in a Bibby or a small single person tent. This was inside of the cabin at the camp. The Bibby of the zipper apparently broke off and the staff member used the zip tie to enclose the tent instead. That staff member told authorities that they believe that quote, he and the camp were responsible for the boys passing. When the staff member was asked what they could have done differently, they said that quote, I could have opened the boys tent and repositioned him. Staff members were supposed to check on campers at midnight, 3:00am and 6:00am. And around 3:00am on February 3rd, staff members said that they heard heavy breathing and quote mumbling coming from the boy's baby. However, they did nothing. The same staff member did a check around 6:00am and said that The boy was still breathing at 6:00am. The staff member did a check on the boy and said that he was certain he heard breathing, but said the boy was quote, no longer heavily breathing. Law enforcement was dispatched to the camp around 8:00am when the boy was found unresponsive. The staff member said, quote, my actions that night was to perform night checks. That was my responsibility, which I failed on. I do feel like the baby had a lot to do with it. Suffocation is always a possibility when equipment is used wrong. The trails Carolina Camp regularly made new campers sleep in the bivy with alarms on the zippers when they first arrived at the camp until they are deemed safe enough to sleep outside of it. Cold case solved: Alex and Susan Carter #coldcasesolved #coldcasetiktok #coldcasessolved #deathbedconfessions #coldcasetok #truecrimecommunity #truecrimetok #unsolvedcases #unsolvedcasefiles #unsolvedcasesolved #truecrime #foryou #truecrimestoryCold case solved: Alex and Susan Carter #coldcasesolved #coldcasetiktok #coldcasessolved #deathbedconfessions #coldcasetok #truecrimecommunity #truecrimetok #unsolvedcases #unsolvedcasefiles #unsolvedcasesolved #truecrime #foryou #truecrimestory
voice_to_text: Thanks to a deathbed confession, a nearly 24 year old cold case was closed this week when the bodies of a missing girl and her mother were found. Ten year old Natasha Alex Carter and her mother Susan disappeared from their home in Beckley, West Virginia in August 2000. But at first police initially reported that Alex may have been abducted by her mother. In a press release from December 2021 about the case, the FBI Pittsburgh said quote at the time of their disappearance, Susan Carter and Alex's father were having a custody dispute and Alex moved in with her mother and mother's new husband, which it's not confirmed that it was actually her mother's new husband, but they moved in and then not long after that, Susan and Alex disappeared. But while it was initially suspected as a parental abduction by Susan after the two remained missing, an investigation into other possibilities ensued, but unfortunately the case went cold. In 2021, the FBI reopened the cold case and started looking into the man Susan and Alex were living with, Larry Webb, which is of his home. Were done in 2022 and 2023 and they found a bullet embedded in the wall of what was Alex's bedroom. Bullet was tested for DNA and it confirmed that blood on it belonged to Alex. In October 2023, Larry Webb was indicted on first degree murder charges for Alex's death, despite Alex and Susan's bodies never being found due to his deteriorating health. Though Webb was Not arrested until April 12th, 2024, but since then he was being held without bond. On Monday he had a medical episode, after which, in a quote, come to Jesus moment on his deathbed, he confessed to authorities what he had done. Upclaimed that on August 8th, 2000, he had gotten into an argument with Susan over money. He said he was missing some cash and believed that she had taken it and spent it. The argument escalated and he shot her, and then he ended up shooting Alex so there would be no witnesses. Webb then wrapped their bodies in bed linens and placed them in the basement that night. Over the next two nights, he dug a shallow grave in the woods on his property, eventually burying them in his clothes and then walking free for the next 20 years. On April 22nd, 2024, Larry Webb died at Mount Olive Correctional Complex, and six hours later, Susan and Alex's remains were found at his property in Beckley. Fortunately, now that Webb is dead, he cannot be charged in connection to their deaths. At least now they have been found and can be properly laid to rest. Alex's father, Rick Lafferty, said after the discovery, quote, it's kind of a sad day, but also a happy day because I can bring my baby home. Rest in peace, Alex and Susan.

voice_to_text: US health officials are warning the public after a Colorado woman was left paralyzed by a can of soup. Twenty three year old Claudia de Albuquerque Salada was left paralyzed in on a ventilator two weeks after consuming the contaminated food. She was diagnosed with botulism which caused dizziness, double vision and trouble breathing. Health department tested soup from the store's Albuquerque Salada frequented and they came back negative. Now they're reminding the public of the dangers of mishandling leftover food, advising people to store perishables at 40 degrees Fahrenheit or colder, ensure food is completely heated through and avoid leaving food out for more than an hour.

voice_to_text: The man in that video, Sergio Maria Lima de Santana, died while he was vlogging when a support being collapsed in the zipline that he was on came crashing to the ground. Thirty nine year old Sergio was an average guy and he was on vacation at a resort in Brazil called the Kenoa Cabrata Resort. On that day, Sergio decided he wanted to make use of the zipline that was on property. After all, it looked like a beautiful, fun thing to go do, he had no idea that a part of the zipline support structure was weak. And tragically, Sergio heading down the zipline was a straw that broke the camel. Or ziplines. Back in the video, Sergio can be seen smiling, hollering and enjoying his last moments on earth before suddenly the zipline collapses and he plummets to his death. This is an actual picture of local investigators checking out the collapse support beam. After this incident, officials in the local city banned all ziplines for the moment and eventually the 35 year old owner of the zipline company was charged with manslaughter in Sergio's death. I don't know exactly who got charged with water convicted of what in this case, but this video is definitely haunting, disturbing and it was captured sadly in multiple angles.

Call her daddy podcast host Alex Cooper is officially married today. Alex let her daddy gang in on a little secret she had been keeping. On April 6th, she tied the knot with Matt Kaplan, and Vogue covered her wedding and it looks gorgeous. Alex and Matt had an intimate beachside wedding in Riviera Maya. Unlike most brides who have their father walk them down the aisle, she chose to walk herself. Alex told Vogue at the beginning of the wedding planning, I really rejected the concept of being walked down by a man to be handed to another man. Although, to clarify, I have such an incredible relationship with my father and both of my parents. To me personally, I never loved that tradition. My mom also walked herself down the aisle. So in a sense, I guess my family is doing our own tradition. But one of Alex's family members was part of the wedding, being her brother Grant. Grant officiated the wedding. Alex and Matt could not have tied the knot without their goldendoodles, aka their fur babies, Henry and Bruce. Henry and Bruce were their ringbearers, and they're so adorable. Their suits, I love this. Henry and Bruce even have their own sand statues, and this sand statue of their pups were up throughout the weekend. Another tradition that Alex broke was a first dance. That's due to her and Matt both having two left feet. So instead of doing a first dance, they decided to do A first shot with their guests, and Alex wore a beautiful custom Daniel Franco ball gown. Their wedding and reception looks like a dream, and while most brides may say their wedding day is a blur, it's quite the opposite for Alex Cooper. Alex said that she and Matt were intentional in making sure that they were present. Alex says that there is no detail or moment that she won't remember. Congratulations to the newlyweds.
